radiographic_examinations.findings: severe atherosclerosis in 2 vessels, 95% stenosis in the mid portion of the right coronary artery with 75% stenosis at the crux and 95% stenosis in the proximal portion of the left anterior descending coronary artery, continuing on to 2 other 50% stenoses.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Nine months later, he experienced restenosis in the paclitaxel-eluting stent in the proximal left anterior descending coronary artery and was treated with a rapamycin-eluting stent.

radiographic_examinations.findings: critical stenosis at the left main coronary artery.
